Binomial coefficients count subsets of prescribed size from a given set. A related combinatorial problem is to count <a href="multiset">multiset</a>s of prescribed size with elements drawn from a given set, that is, to count the number of ways to select a certain number of elements from a given set with the possibility of selecting the same element repeatedly. The resulting numbers are called "<a href="Multiset%23Counting%20multisets">multiset coefficients</a>"; the number of ways to "multichoose" (i.e., choose with replacement) "k" items from an "n" element set is denoted formula_188.

To avoid ambiguity and confusion with "n"'s main denotation in this article,<br> let "f" = "n" = "r" + ("k" – 1) and "r" = "f" – ("k" – 1).

